I was using the '=' as default operator, but that does not work for the text type. The UPM allowed me to install my add-on with this configuration and then not show my filter in the UI. Changing the default operator to '~' fixed my problem.

{code:java}
{
    key: "myKey",
    name: {
        value: "Name"
    },
    keyConfigurations: [
        {
            propertyKey: "myProperty",
            extractions: [
                {
                    objectName: "myObject",
                    type: "text",
                    alias: "myAlias",
                    uiSupport: {
                        defaultOperator: "=",
                        dataUri: "/my/filter/url",
                        valueType: "string",
                        name: {
                            value: "My Search Name"
                        }
                    }
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}
{code}

